# Supabase Egress Audit â€” Findings & Fix Plan

## Context
Full codebase audit for patterns that will blow Supabase egress (database transfer + storage bandwidth). Three areas analyzed: DB query payloads, storage/image serving, and client-side refetch behavior.

**Verdict: Yes, this codebase has several patterns that will cause excessive egress at scale.**

---

## CRITICAL â€” Fix These First

### 1. `content` (Lexical JSON) returned in ALL feed/list queries
Every feed endpoint returns full post content (5-100KB per post) even though list views only show previews. A `JOURNAL_METADATA_SELECT` constant exists but is **never used**.

| Affected | File | Lines |
|----------|------|-------|
| Public feed | `server/services/getService.js` | L441 |
| User journals | `server/services/getService.js` | L821 |
| Visited profile | `server/services/getService.js` | L917 |
| Bookmarks | `server/services/getService.js` | L1117-1129 |
| Repost sources | `server/services/getService.js` | L95-99 |
| Following feed RPC | `server/sql/following_feed.sql` | L52 |
| For-you feed RPC | `server/sql/personalized_feed.sql` | L102 |
| Related posts RPC | `server/sql/discovery.sql` | L68 |
| Explore interests | `server/services/exploreInterestsService.js` | L38-83 (8 parallel pgvector scans, up to 64 posts with full content) |

**Fix:** Use `JOURNAL_METADATA_SELECT` (already defined at L35-48) in all list endpoints. Remove `content` from all SQL RPC return signatures. Only return `content` in `getJournalByIdService` (single post detail).

**Estimated savings:** 60-80% of database egress.

---

### 2. No CDN in front of Supabase Storage
All 5 storage buckets (`avatars`, `background`, `journal-images`, `story-covers`, media gallery) serve images directly from `https://<project>.supabase.co/storage/...`. No CDN configured anywhere. Every image request = full Supabase storage egress.

Avatar URLs are embedded in every feed response, comment, notification, and repost â€” meaning 5-20 Supabase Storage hits per feed page load across all users.

**Fix:** Put Cloudflare (free tier) or another CDN in front of Supabase Storage via a custom subdomain (e.g., `media.iskrib.com`).

**Estimated savings:** 70-90% of storage egress once cache warms.

---

### 3. `QueryClient` has zero default configuration
`client/src/main.jsx` L9: `new QueryClient()` with no defaults means:
- `staleTime: 0` â€” every query is immediately stale
- `refetchOnWindowFocus: true` â€” every tab switch refetches all active queries
- Any `useQuery` that forgets to set its own `staleTime` silently refetches on every render

**Fix:**
```js
const queryClient = new QueryClient({
  defaultOptions: {
    queries: {
      staleTime: 1000 * 60 * 5,        // 5 min default
      refetchOnWindowFocus: false,
    }
  }
});
```

---

### 4. Broad `invalidateQueries` on every social action
`client/src/utils/useMutation.js` L95-97, L195-197, L455-459: Every like, bookmark, reaction, repost, and comment invalidates `['journals']` which matches ALL feed queries. If a user has scrolled 5 pages deep, this triggers 5 sequential refetches per feed variant â€” potentially 15+ API calls from a single like.

**Fix:** Use optimistic updates only (already partially implemented) and either remove `onSettled` invalidation or scope it to the specific active feed query key.

